  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version (output of `vyper --version`): 0.3.8+commit.8ebabc5c\r\n* OS: GNU\r\n* Python Version (output of `python --version`): Python 3.10.9\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nThis file compiles fine with `vyper`, but fails if you try to load it with `boa`.\r\n```\r\n@external\r\ndef bug() -> uint256:\r\n  x: uint256 = 392\r\n  y: uint256 = 19\r\n  return shift(x, y)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe [docs](https://docs.vyperlang.org/en/stable/built-in-functions.html#shift) for `shift` list the following type:\r\n`shift(x: uint256, _shift: int128) â†’ uint256`\r\n\r\nThe [implementation](https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/blob/8ebabc5ce277942ee470845e2d04df5f8a2e6ad6/vyper/builtins/functions.py#L1459) is different again, allowing any integer type (whereas boa complains for non-int128).\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nDecide on the semantics and make vyper, boa, and the docs consistent.\r\n",
